<headline>Severe Weather Statement issued July 26 at 4:28PM EDT until July 26 at 5:30PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...THE SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING FOR
SOUTH CENTRAL APPOMATTOX...NORTHWESTERN CHARLOTTE AND SOUTHEASTERN
CAMPBELL COUNTIES WILL EXPIRE AT 430 PM EDT...
The storm which prompted the warning has moved out of the area and
been replaced with another severe thunderstorm warning for eastern
Campbell.
Therefore, the warning will be allowed to expire.  However gusty
winds are still possible with this thunderstorm.
Remember, a Severe Thunderstorm Warning still remains in effect for
South central Appomattox County...Northwestern Charlotte County
and Southeastern Campbell County in central Virginia until 515 pm...</description>
